review-text:
Pros:
- beautiful beach;
- tables with chairs;
- you can bring your own meat and rent a grill;
- after sunset there was music, a show, and fireworks.

Cons:
- dirty sea with plastic bags and other garbage floating in large quantities;
- we found out in advance whether we could bring our own meat and cook it ourselves. We were told that we couldn't cook on our own grill, but they showed us a menu that said that the restaurant could cook our meat for an extra fee. On day X we arrived and were told that they wouldn't cook the meat. The staff wasn't interested in helping us at all. Eventually, thanks to our persistence, they called the administrator, who said that we could use the grill for an extra fee.
- There is a "zoo" on the premises, the animals are kept in small cages. The deer are in an enclosure that has nothing but concrete. A terrible sight.
